President Donald J. Trump and First Lady Melania Trump express their condolences to those affected by the boating accident on Table Rock Lake in Missouri. The incident involved a tourism boat that sank during a storm, resulting in the deaths of 17 people and injuries to several others. The President and First Lady offer their prayers to the victims and their families. They also commend the bravery of the first responders and dive crews who have saved many lives. The Administration has been in contact with Governor Parson and other officials, and the President will stay updated on the situation.